The kidnapped Adamawa State Chairman of the National Union of Local Government Employees (NULGE), Hammanjulde Gatugel, has regained freedom. Gatugel was kidnapped by unknown gunmen at his Mayo-Belwa residence, Saturday, has regained his freedom. A source close to his family said , he was released by the kidnappers about 12:30am today (Sunday),. How much was paid but for now I can’t tell how much was paid as ransom before he was released.” Adamawa state Police Public Relations Officer, Suleiman Nguroje, who confirmed the development said the chairman was released unharmed. Nguroje however did not say if ransom was paid for his release A hot chase mounted by police, he says, scared the kidnappers into releasing their victim. Shortly after the abduction of Hammanjulde Gatugel on Saturday, Nguroje had confirmed four people were nabbed in connection with it. He had clarified that the suspects were captured by the special unit of state command of anti-kidnappers deployed in the region to rescue the chairman of the NULGE